<div id="review_1359706314" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1359706314" />
    <a title="Terri Lynn" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5699299-terri-lynn"><img alt="Terri Lynn" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1329255932p2/5699299.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1359706314?book_show_action=true">Aug 09, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Terri Lynn" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Terri Lynn" href="/user/show/5699299-terri-lynn">Terri Lynn</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5699299-terri-lynn?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5699299-terri-lynn?shelf=mystery-suspense-thrillers">mystery-suspense-thrillers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1359706314" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16007573159239936680">Mike Baye, a transplant doctor, and his wife Tia Baye, a lawyer, seem to have it all- nice home in the suburbs, plenty of money, nice vehicles, good jobs, living spouses, and two kids- 11 year old Jill and 16 year old Adam but under the surface, as always in Harlan Coben novels, there is an undercurrent of danger, dysfunction, and evil. <br/><br/>Adam&apos;s close friend Spencer Hill committed suicide using legal sedatives stolen from his parents&apos;medicine cabinet 4 months earlier. Adam has changed and had begu</span>
  <span id="freeText16007573159239936680" style="display:none">Mike Baye, a transplant doctor, and his wife Tia Baye, a lawyer, seem to have it all- nice home in the suburbs, plenty of money, nice vehicles, good jobs, living spouses, and two kids- 11 year old Jill and 16 year old Adam but under the surface, as always in Harlan Coben novels, there is an undercurrent of danger, dysfunction, and evil. <br /><br />Adam's close friend Spencer Hill committed suicide using legal sedatives stolen from his parents'medicine cabinet 4 months earlier. Adam has changed and had begun to change even before that. He is becoming a stranger to his parents and beloved little sister. Tia decides enough is enough and she and Mike have the tech guy from her law office set up spyware on Adam's computer and Mike activates the GPS on their son's phone.<br /><br />Thus begins their nightmare- and the nightmares of others. Adam goes missing after Spencer's mother Karen Hill approaches him after school with a photo from a site honoring Spencer that shows that far from being alone the night he died, Spencer was with friends including DJ Huff who is the police chief's bad boy son, and with Adam. Mike almost gets killed when following the signal from his GPS and almost getting to Adam in a teen club where the selling of prescription drugs goes on. <br /><br />Meanwhile, the female head of the police detectives struggles against a sexist colleague as they deal with two murdered women- one with her face destroyed who they can't identify- and who were made to look like hookers, both by a creepy man assisted by a woman named Pietra who had seen her own family murdered and seems to not like what the man is doing. <br /><br />This is a complicated story with issues ranging from a boy who needs a kidney who was born of a rape his mom never reported to a teacher who humiliated a little girl only to incur the wrath of both of her parents. It will definitely keep your attention.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16007573159239936680" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


