        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer41479571" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14594516208368215977">I am a fan of Harlan Coben&apos;s, but this wasn&apos;t my favorite of his books. Yes, the plot had many unexpected twists and turns and kept me guessing up until the end. But I thought he wove too many stories together, making it hard to follow. Also, I thought the story line with the daughter was wrapped up a little too neatly at the end. If you&apos;re a parent, this book explores some current moral dilemmas in parenting--namely, how much is it permissible to invade your child&apos;s privacy? Coben blends his ch</span>
  <span id="freeText14594516208368215977" style="display:none">I am a fan of Harlan Coben's, but this wasn't my favorite of his books. Yes, the plot had many unexpected twists and turns and kept me guessing up until the end. But I thought he wove too many stories together, making it hard to follow. Also, I thought the story line with the daughter was wrapped up a little too neatly at the end. If you're a parent, this book explores some current moral dilemmas in parenting--namely, how much is it permissible to invade your child's privacy? Coben blends his characters from one book to another, and I was happy to see one of my favorites, Hester Crimstein, make a return appearance. Overall, a quick and fun read, but not his best.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14594516208368215977" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

